---
/**
 * Semantic page structure component that enforces proper HTML5 semantics
 * and heading hierarchy for documentation pages.
 *
 * This component ensures:
 * - Proper main landmark for page content
 * - Section structure for content organization
 * - Skip navigation support for accessibility
 * - Proper heading hierarchy without H1 conflicts
 *
 * Why this component exists:
 * - Creates the primary main landmark required for accessibility
 * - Provides a consistent entry point for page content across the site
 * - Ensures proper focus management for skip navigation functionality
 * - Establishes the semantic boundary between navigation and main content
 * - Offers consistent styling and layout for all documentation pages
 *
 * Technical implementation:
 * - Uses semantic HTML5 main element with proper ARIA labeling
 * - Includes tabindex="-1" to support programmatic focus (skip links)
 * - Provides proper focus indicators for keyboard navigation
 * - Uses CSS custom properties for consistent theming
 *
 * @example
 * ```astro
 * <PageMain>
 *   <h1>Page Title</h1>
 *   <p>Main page content...</p>
 * </PageMain>
 * ```
 */

/**
 * Configuration options for the PageMain component.
 * Currently this component accepts no props as it serves as a
 * standard wrapper for all main content.
 */
export interface PageMainProps {
  // No props currently needed - this component provides
  // a standard main wrapper for all documentation pages
}
---

<main id="main-content" tabindex="-1" role="main" aria-label="Main content">
  <slot />
</main>

<style>
  main {
    /* Ensure proper focus styles for skip navigation */
    outline: none;
  }

  main:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--sl-color-accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* Ensure proper spacing and layout */
  main {
    min-height: calc(100vh - var(--sl-nav-height, 4rem));
  }
</style>
